Package nusri.fyp.demo.service.img_sender.roboflow

Class RoboflowService

java.lang.Object
nusri.fyp.demo.service.img_sender.roboflow.RoboflowService
@Service public class RoboflowService extends Object
Service that encapsulates the logic for making inference requests to the Roboflow platform, including both synchronous and asynchronous calls for image processing.
This service sends Base64-encoded images to Roboflow, receives prediction results, and processes the results (including visualizations and object counting). Key Points:
  • Synchronous and Asynchronous Processing:
    The service supports both blocking (synchronous) and non-blocking (asynchronous) image processing using Roboflow.
  • Prediction Handling:
    The predictions returned by Roboflow are processed, mapped to class names from the database, and returned as a list of SinglePrediction objects.

      RoboflowService(RequestSenderOfOKHttp requestSenderOfOKHttp, ObjectRepository objectRepository, ActionRepository actionRepository, RoboflowConfig roboflowConfig)

      requestSenderOfOKHttp - The HTTP request sender for Roboflow API requests.
      objectRepository - The repository used for object-to-id mapping.

  • Method Details

    • sendImg

      public List<SinglePrediction> sendImg(String base64String)
      Synchronously sends a Base64-encoded image to Roboflow and retrieves predictions.
      This method sends the image to the Roboflow API, retrieves the predictions, processes them, and returns a list of predictions with mapped class labels.
      Parameters:
      base64String - The Base64-encoded image string to be sent to Roboflow.
      Returns:
      A list of SinglePrediction objects representing the predictions from Roboflow.

    • sendImgAsync

      public CompletableFuture<List<AbstractActionObservation>> sendImgAsync(String base64String)
      Asynchronously sends a Base64-encoded image to Roboflow and retrieves predictions.
      This method initiates the image processing asynchronously, allowing non-blocking operations and returns a CompletableFuture that will eventually contain a list of predictions.
      Parameters:
      base64String - The Base64-encoded image string to be sent to Roboflow.
      Returns:
      A CompletableFuture containing a list of AbstractActionObservation objects representing the predictions.

    • buildSpecification

      public static Map<String,Object> buildSpecification()
      Builds the specification for the inference workflow that is sent to Roboflow.
      This method constructs the entire inference workflow, including steps for object detection, visualization, and counting.
      Returns:
      A Map representing the inference workflow specification, which will be serialized into JSON and sent to Roboflow.
